ss=title> Re: Mez</span><hr size=1> You touch that Mob it be breakin mez and goin after the Enc real quick<br>Just stand infront of it and hit Taunt<br>You do it right when the mez breaks it will forget about the Enc and worry about you<br>Atleast this is what we used to do back in the old days of Hate and fear<br> <p><center><font face="Times NewRoman"size=4color="#c9c9c9">Saraleb Bloodarrow</font><br><fontface="TimesNewRoman"size=3><i>Outrider of Tunare</i></font><br><a href"http://pub47.ezboard.com/bsanctimony"><imgsrc="http://www.warlordsofzek.com/temerity/sig.gif" border="0"></a><br><font size=2 face="times new roman">Trust me...Arrows Hurt</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/urosvineer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rosvineer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/14/02 4:42:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mez</span><hr size=1> Flame lick has a small dot so will break mez.  Snare is a good one since it does not break mez.  Ranger and druid root will break because of the damage is does.  Snare and taunt is about all a ranger can use on a mezed mob to make it chase you when mez breaks rather than the chanter.  <br><br>Once mez breaks and you want to gain agro real quick, re-snare, flame lick, whatever nuke and or dot you have and melee/kick.  You should be able to keep the chanter (or any other you want to save) from getting hit for more than one round of combat.<br><br>You can also root an unmezed mob to control agro.  A rooted mob will usually attack the closest PC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/usnowtalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snowtalon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/21/02 7:59:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mez</span><hr size=1> Snare is awesome to use before breaking mez, if main tank our Taunt sucks, I snare 3 times in a row then cast root to break mez then start melee after root breaks, a single snare is enough to put you above the ench on hate list if the ench has only mezzed 1 time, if the ench has slowed, tashed, or mezzed multiple times takes 2 or 3 snares to get the aggro above the ench.<br><br>Jolea<br>52 Pathfinder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/beqrangers65329.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeke>Zeke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/23/02 5:30:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mez</span><hr size=1> Here is a nice trick for raids where you need to snare but want to keep the aggro on the main tank(MT). Snare the mob, then cast jolt while the MT is taunting to gain aggro to break mez, nither snare or jolt will break a mez.<br><br>If your the main tank, a successful taunt will put you 1 aggro point above the next highest person with aggro, so if you snare after you taunt a couple of times you will be much higher on the aggro list than anyone else<br><br>Zeke<br>58 Outrider <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </t